for eight seconds?

134
00:20:25,791 --> 00:20:28,817
Money's a good point.
True enough.

135
00:20:30,296 --> 00:20:32,992
If you don't get stomped
winnin' it, huh?

136
00:20:33,132 --> 00:20:34,224
Yeah.

137
00:20:36,002 --> 00:20:39,096
Well, my old man,
he was a bull rider.

138
00:20:40,840 --> 00:20:42,170
Thank you.

139
00:20:42,941 --> 00:20:45,136
Pretty well-known in his day.

140
00:20:45,544 --> 00:20:48,138
Though he kept his secrets
to himself.

141
00:20:49,548 --> 00:20:53,075
Never taught me a thing,
never once come
to see me ride.

142
00:21:04,629 --> 00:21:07,325
Your brother and sister
do right by you?

143
00:21:07,966 --> 00:21:11,402
They did the best they could
after my folks was gone.

144
00:21:13,271 --> 00:21:16,104
Considerin' they didn't
leave us nothin'...

145
00:21:16,441 --> 00:21:18,534
but $24 in a coffee can.

146
00:21:20,111 --> 00:21:22,477
I got me
a year of high school.

147
00:21:23,248 --> 00:21:26,445
That was before
the transmission went
on the pickup.

148
00:21:29,221 --> 00:21:32,918
And then my sis left.
She married a roughneck,
moved to Casper.

149
00:21:34,059 --> 00:21:35,788
And me and my brother...

150
00:21:35,860 --> 00:21:39,387
we went and got ourselves
some work on a ranch
up near Worland.

151
00:21:39,464 --> 00:21:42,399
Till I was 19.
Then he got married.

152
00:21:45,036 --> 00:21:46,970
And no more room for me.

153
00:21:50,375 --> 00:21:54,003
That's how come
me end up here.

154
00:22:04,188 --> 00:22:05,280
What?

155
00:22:07,091 --> 00:22:10,993
Man, that's more words
than you've spoke
in the past two weeks.

156
00:22:11,862 --> 00:22:14,695
Hell, that's the most
I've spoke in a year.

157
00:22:20,671 --> 00:22:23,003
But my dad,
he was a fine roper.

158
00:22:24,108 --> 00:22:25,405
Didn't rodeo much, though.

159
00:22:25,476 --> 00:22:28,070
He thought rodeo cowboys
was all fuck-ups.

160
00:22:30,981 --> 00:22:32,642
The hell they are.

161
00:22:34,318 --> 00:22:35,546
Well...

162
00:22:41,458 --> 00:22:42,686
There you go.

163
00:22:44,495 --> 00:22:48,261
I'm spurrin' his guts out!
Wavin' to the girls
in the stands!

164
00:22:48,332 --> 00:22:51,893
He's kickin' me to
high heaven, but he don't
jackboard me! No!

165
00:22:56,106 --> 00:22:58,097
I think my dad was right.

166
00:23:43,319 --> 00:23:45,184
Tent don't look right.

167
00:23:45,888 --> 00:23:48,721
Well, it ain't
goin' nowhere. Let it be.

168
00:23:50,660 --> 00:23:53,128
That harmonica don't sound
quite right either.

169
00:23:53,196 --> 00:23:56,632
That's 'cause
it got kind of flattened
when that mare threw me.

170
00:23:56,699 --> 00:23:58,291
Oh, yeah?
Yeah.

171
00:23:58,901 --> 00:24:01,802
I thought you said
that mare couldn't throw you.

172
00:24:01,871 --> 00:24:03,361
She got lucky.

173
00:24:04,807 --> 00:24:08,334
Yeah, well, if I got lucky,
that harmonica
would've broke in two.

174
00:24:11,813 --> 00:24:16,045
# I know I shall meet you
on that final day #

175
00:24:16,618 --> 00:24:21,612
# Water-walking Jesus,
take me away! ##

176
00:24:23,291 --> 00:24:25,919
Very good.
Oh, yeah.

177
00:24:26,128 --> 00:24:29,222
My mama, she believes
in the Pentecost.

178
00:24:29,297 --> 00:24:30,559
Oh, yeah?

179
00:24:32,734 --> 00:24:34,702
What exactly
is the Pentecost?

180
00:24:34,770 --> 00:24:37,534
I mean, my folks,
they was Methodist.

181
00:24:38,974 --> 00:24:40,464
The Pentecost.

182
00:24:40,776 --> 00:24:43,267
I don't know, I don't know
what the Pentecost is.

183
00:24:43,345 --> 00:24:47,805
Mom never explained it to me.
I guess it's when
the world ends...

184
00:24:47,983 --> 00:24:51,043
and fellas like you and me,
we march off to hell.

185
00:24:52,220 --> 00:24:53,812
Speak for yourself.

186
00:24:53,889 --> 00:24:57,416
You may be a sinner,
but I ain't yet had
the opportunity.

187
00:25:00,028 --> 00:25:01,359
Thank you.

188
00:25:04,232 --> 00:25:06,132
Shit!

189
00:25:08,069 --> 00:25:09,969
I'm gonna go up
to the sheep now.

190
00:25:10,038 --> 00:25:11,528
Give 'em hell.

191
00:25:17,646 --> 00:25:19,169
No, I'm...

192
00:25:21,315 --> 00:25:24,842
