but ours.

210
00:32:16,290 --> 00:32:18,190
You know I ain't queer.

211
00:32:19,260 --> 00:32:20,625
Me, neither.

212
00:33:35,468 --> 00:33:36,799
I'm sorry.

213
00:33:37,971 --> 00:33:39,495
It's all right.

214
00:33:41,708 --> 00:33:43,198
It's all right.

215
00:33:43,276 --> 00:33:45,335
Lie back. Come on.

216
00:34:48,507 --> 00:34:49,667
Twist.

217
00:34:50,309 --> 00:34:53,073
Your Uncle Harold's in
the hospital with pneumonia.

218
00:34:53,145 --> 00:34:55,443
Docs don't expect
he'll make it.

219
00:34:56,382 --> 00:34:59,476
Your ma sent me to tell you,
so here I am.

220
00:35:02,621 --> 00:35:03,883
Bad news.

221
00:35:05,724 --> 00:35:08,386
There ain't nothin' I can do
about it up here, I guess.

222
00:35:08,460 --> 00:35:12,021
There's not much you can do
about it down there, neither.

223
00:35:14,800 --> 00:35:17,234
Not unless you can
cure pneumonia.

224
00:35:50,301 --> 00:35:52,531
God damn! Jesus!

225
00:35:52,637 --> 00:35:55,504
Them sheep will drift
if I don't get back
up there tonight!

226
00:35:55,573 --> 00:35:58,565
You'll get
pitched off your mount
in a storm like this.

227
00:35:58,643 --> 00:36:00,941
You'll wish
you hadn't tried it!

228
00:36:01,712 --> 00:36:03,646
It's too cold! Close it up!

229
00:36:13,424 --> 00:36:15,949
What are we
supposed to do now, huh?

230
00:36:16,094 --> 00:36:20,326
Get on in there and
untangle 'em Chilean sheep
out of ours, I guess.

231
00:36:22,200 --> 00:36:23,861
Oh, where is it? Shit!

232
00:36:28,106 --> 00:36:31,269
God, half the goddamn
paint brands have wore off!

233
00:36:32,243 --> 00:36:36,475
We gotta try.
The least we can do is get
the count right for Aguirre.

234
00:36:36,547 --> 00:36:39,345
Fuck Aguirre!
Oh, yeah, fuck Aguirre.

235
00:36:39,484 --> 00:36:42,351
What if we need to
work for him again?
You think of that?

236
00:36:42,420 --> 00:36:44,650
We gotta
stick this out, Jack.

237
00:37:00,504 --> 00:37:04,031
You'll run them
sheep off again
if you don't quiet down.

238
00:37:40,510 --> 00:37:42,239
What are you doing?

239
00:37:43,513 --> 00:37:45,378
Aguirre came by again.

240
00:37:45,882 --> 00:37:48,350
Says my uncle didn't die
after all.

241
00:37:49,052 --> 00:37:50,747
Says bring 'em down.

242
00:37:50,820 --> 00:37:53,914
Bring 'em down, why?
It's the middle of August.

243
00:37:54,191 --> 00:37:57,354
Says there's a storm comin',
movin' in from the Pacific.

244
00:37:57,427 --> 00:37:59,190
Worse than this one.

245
00:37:59,896 --> 00:38:03,194
That snow barely
