Now it's like seein' the Pope.

964
01:44:59,821 --> 01:45:01,584
Jack, I got to work.

965
01:45:04,692 --> 01:45:07,593
In them earlier days,
I'd just quit the job.

966
01:45:10,330 --> 01:45:11,661
You...

967
01:45:12,332 --> 01:45:15,597
You forget what it's like
bein' broke all the time.

968
01:45:19,206 --> 01:45:21,504
You ever hear
of child support?

969
01:45:25,379 --> 01:45:27,711
I'll tell you this,
I can't quit this one...

970
01:45:27,781 --> 01:45:29,772
and I can't get the time off.

971
01:45:33,720 --> 01:45:35,711
It was hard enough
gettin' this time.

972
01:45:35,789 --> 01:45:37,518
The trade-off was August.

973
01:45:41,662 --> 01:45:43,527
Well, you got a better idea?

974
01:45:46,333 --> 01:45:47,732
I did, once.

975
01:45:49,937 --> 01:45:51,427
You did, once.

976
01:45:56,276 --> 01:45:58,801
Well, have you been to Mexico,
Jack Twist?

977
01:46:01,481 --> 01:46:05,008
'Cause I hear what they got
in Mexico for boys like you.

978
01:46:06,753 --> 01:46:10,314
Hell, yes,
I've been to Mexico.
Is that a fucking problem?

979
01:46:18,398 --> 01:46:21,798
I'm going to tell you this
one time, Jack fucking Twist.

980
01:46:21,867 --> 01:46:23,630
And I ain't foolin'.

981
01:46:24,971 --> 01:46:28,634
What I don't know, all them
things that I don't know...

982
01:46:29,041 --> 01:46:31,942
could get you killed
if I come to know them.

983
01:46:36,115 --> 01:46:37,639
I ain't jokin'.

984
01:46:42,455 --> 01:46:45,117
Yeah, well try this one,
and I'll say it just once.

985
01:46:45,191 --> 01:46:47,887
Go ahead!
I'll tell you what.

986
01:46:47,960 --> 01:46:49,427
We could have had
a good life together.

987
01:46:49,495 --> 01:46:52,692
Fucking real good life.
Had us a place of our own!

988
01:46:53,733 --> 01:46:55,792
But you didn't want it, Ennis.

989
01:46:55,868 --> 01:46:58,666
So what we got now
is Brokeback Mountain!

990
01:47:00,906 --> 01:47:04,205
Everything's built on that!
That's all we got, boy.
Fucking all.

991
01:47:04,277 --> 01:47:06,905
So I hope you know that,
if you don't never know
the rest!

992
01:47:06,979 --> 01:47:09,243
God damn it.
You count the damn
few times...

993
01:47:09,315 --> 01:47:11,112
that we have been together
in nearly 20 years...

994
01:47:11,183 --> 01:47:13,310
and you measure
the short fucking leash
you keep me on...

995
01:47:13,386 --> 01:47:16,014
and then you ask me
about Mexico and you tell me
you'll kill me...

996
01:47:16,088 --> 01:47:19,148
for needin' somethin'
I don't hardly never get!

997
01:47:21,727 --> 01:47:24,662
You have no idea
how bad it gets!

998
01:47:28,200 --> 01:47:31,134
And I'm not you!
I can't make it...

999
01:47:31,202 --> 01:47:34,729
on a couple of high-altitude
fucks once or twice a year!

1000
01:47:37,309 --> 01:47:39,607
You are too much
for me, Ennis.

1001
01:47:40,312 --> 01:47:42,439
You son of a whoreson bitch!

1002
01:47:44,616 --> 01:47:46,846
I wish I knew how to quit you!

1003
01:47:49,487 --> 01:47:51,216
Then why don't you?

1004
01:47:54,159 --> 01:47:56,593
Why don't you just
let me be, huh?

1005
01:47:58,663 --> 01:48:01,655
It's because of you, Jack,
that I'm like this.

1006
01:48:05,303 --> 01:48:06,702
I'm nothin'.

1007
01:48:07,372 --> 01:48:08,771
I'm nowhere.

1008
01:48:13,445 --> 01:48:16,073
It's okay.
Get the fuck off me!

1009
01:48:23,154 --> 01:48:25,748
It's all right.
It's all right.

1010
01:48:26,825 --> 01:48:28,417
Damn you, Ennis.

1011
01:48:29,761 --> 01:48:32,355
I just can't stand
this anymore, Jack.

1012
01:48:42,873 --> 01:48:46,331
Come on now, you're sleepin'
on your feet like a horse.

1013
01:48:48,679 --> 01:48:51,842
My mama used to say that to me
when I was little.

1014
01:48:52,883 --> 01:48:54,578
And sing to me.

1015
01:49:08,432 --> 01:49:09,831
I got to go.

1016
01:49:12,770 --> 01:49:14,704
See you in the morning.

1017
01:49:55,611 --> 01:49:57,704
##

1018
01:50:09,859 --> 01:50:11,190
Excuse me.

1019
01:50:16,265 --> 01:50:17,323
Hey.

1020
01:50:18,301 --> 01:50:19,791
Ennis Del Mar.

1021
01:50:23,372 --> 01:50:24,896
Where you been?

1022
01:50:26,876 --> 01:50:28,400
Here and there.

1023
01:50:31,080 --> 01:50:34,208
I left word for you
with Steve at the ranch.

1024
01:50:35,117 --> 01:50:38,484
And you must've got those
notes I left at your place.

1025
01:50:42,291 --> 01:50:45,089
Looks like I got the message,
in any case.

1026
01:50:47,330 --> 01:50:48,422
Carl?

1027
01:50:50,266 --> 01:50:52,234
Yeah, Carl's nice.

1028
01:50:53,002 --> 01:50:54,492
He even talks.

1029
01:50:57,706 --> 01:50:59,173
Good for you.

1030
01:51:01,543 --> 01:51:02,635
Yeah.

1031
01:51:05,647 --> 01:51:07,046
Good for me.

1032
01:51:13,488 --> 01:51:15,786
I don't get you,
Ennis Del Mar.

1033
01:51:21,129 --> 01:51:22,460
I'm sorry.

1034
01:51:30,939 --> 01:51:33,464
I was probably
no fun anyways, was I?

1035
01:51:36,945 --> 01:51:39,880
Ennis, girls don't
fall in love with fun.

1036
01:52:22,623 --> 01:52:26,286
<i>Hello.
Hello, this is Ennis Del Mar.</i>

1037
01:52:29,597 --> 01:52:31,224
Who? Who is this?

1038
01:52:32,800 --> 01:52:35,598
Ennis Del Mar.
I'm an old buddy of Jack's.

1039
01:52:36,704 --> 01:52:38,797
<i>Jack used to mention you.</i>

1040
01:52:39,173 --> 01:52:42,870
You're the fishing buddy
or the hunting buddy,
I know that.

1041
01:52:43,944 --> 01:52:45,707
Would have let you know
what happened...

1042
01:52:45,779 --> 01:52:48,304
but I wasn't sure
about your name or address.

1043
01:52:48,382 --> 01:52:51,317
Jack kept his friends'
addresses in his head.

1044
01:52:53,220 --> 01:52:56,155
That's why I'm callin',
to see what happened.

1045
01:52:58,158 --> 01:52:59,682
Oh, yeah.

1046
01:53:02,129 --> 01:53:05,064
Jack was pumpin' up a flat
on the truck...

1047
01:53:05,165 --> 01:53:07,895
out on a back road,
when the tire blew up.

1048
01:53:08,035 --> 01:53:10,936
The rim of the tire slammed
into his face...

1049
01:53:11,138 --> 01:53:15,040
broke his nose and jaw
and knocked him unconscious
on his back.

1050
01:53:16,309 --> 01:53:19,767
<i>By the time somebody
come along, he'd drowned
in his own blood.</i>

1051
01:53:20,880 --> 01:53:22,871
<i>He was only 39 years old.</i>

1052
01:53:27,487 --> 01:53:29,921
<i>Hello? Hello?</i>

1053
01:53:31,157 --> 01:53:32,385
<i>Hello.</i>

1054
01:53:36,029 --> 01:53:38,020
Was he buried down there?

1055
01:53:38,765 --> 01:53:40,198
We put a stone up.

1056
01:53:40,667 --> 01:53:42,692
He was cremated,
like he wanted.

1057
01:53:42,769 --> 01:53:47,035
Half his ashes was
interred here, the rest was
sent up with his folks.

1058
01:53:48,307 --> 01:53:52,334
He use to say he wanted
his ashes scattered
on Brokeback Mountain...

1059
01:53:52,412 --> 01:53:54,812
<i>but I wasn't sure
where that was.</i>

1060
01:53:55,181 --> 01:53:58,947
<i>I thought
Brokeback Mountain might be
around where he grew up.</i>

1061
01:53:59,018 --> 01:54:00,315
<i>Knowing Jack...</i>

1062
01:54:00,386 --> 01:54:02,650
it might be some
pretend place...

1063
01:54:02,722 --> 01:54:05,919
where bluebirds sing
and there's a whiskey spring.

1064
01:54:08,895 --> 01:54:10,328
No, ma'am...

1065
01:54:11,397 --> 01:54:14,525
we was herdin' sheep
on Brokeback one summer...

1066
01:54:15,168 --> 01:54:16,567
<i>back in '63.</i>

1067
01:54:26,011 --> 01:54:28,707
Well, he said
it was his favorite place.

1068
01:54:30,082 --> 01:54:33,279
I thought he meant to
get drunk. He drank a lot.

1069
01:54:36,488 --> 01:54:39,355
Is his folks still up
in Lightning Flat?

1070
01:54:40,025 --> 01:54:42,721
<i>They'll be there
till the day they die.</i>

1071
01:54:47,766 --> 01:54:49,734
Thank you for your time.

1072
01:54:50,602 --> 01:54:52,194
<i>I sure am sorry.</i>

1073
01:54:53,438 --> 01:54:55,201
<i>We was good friends.</i>

1074
01:55:02,380 --> 01:55:04,610
Get in touch with his folks.

1075
01:55:04,683 --> 01:55:08,483
I suppose they'd appreciate it
if his wishes was carried out.

1076
01:55:10,322 --> 01:55:12,290
About the ashes, I mean.

1077
01:56:13,083 --> 01:56:16,519
Want a cup of coffee,
don't you?
Piece of cherry cake?

1078
01:56:16,587 --> 01:56:18,145
Yes, ma'am,
I'll have a cup of coffee...

1079
01:56:18,222 --> 01:56:21,385
but I can't eat no cake
just now. Thank you.

1080
01:56:30,067 --> 01:56:32,228
I feel awful bad about Jack.

1081
01:56:35,072 --> 01:56:36,403
Thank you.

1082
01:56:38,375 --> 01:56:41,173
I can't begin to tell you
how bad I feel.

1083
01:56:44,180 --> 01:56:46,080
I knew him a long time.

1084
01:56:48,985 --> 01:56:50,953
I come by to say that...

1085
01:56:51,621 --> 01:56:55,250
if you want me to take his
ashes up there on Brokeback...

1086
01:56:55,992 --> 01:56:58,426
like his wife said
he wanted to...

1087
01:56:59,195 --> 01:57:00,992
then I'll be happy to.

1088
01:57:04,100 --> 01:57:05,829
I'll tell you what.

1089
01:57:06,903 --> 01:57:09,303
I know where
Brokeback Mountain is.

1090
01:57:10,573 --> 01:57:14,703
Thought he was too goddamn
special to be buried
in the family plot.

1091
01:57:18,114 --> 01:57:19,843
Jack used to say...

1092
01:57:20,683 --> 01:57:23,345
"Ennis Del Mar,"
he used to say.

1093
01:57:25,021 --> 01:57:28,286
"I'm gonna bring him up here
one of these days...

1094
01:57:28,925 --> 01:57:31,860
"and we'll lick this
damn ranch into shape."

1095
01:57:33,296 --> 01:57:35,127
He had some
half-baked notion...

1096
01:57:35,198 --> 01:57:37,792
the two of you was gonna
move up here...

1097
01:57:38,268 --> 01:57:39,860
build a cabin...

1098
01:57:40,904 --> 01:57:42,633
help run the place.

1099
01:57:46,209 --> 01:57:47,938
Then, this spring...

1100
01:57:49,545 --> 01:57:52,776
he got another fella
gonna come up here with him...

1101
01:57:54,449 --> 01:57:57,646
build the place,
help run the ranch.

1102
01:57:58,654 --> 01:58:03,091
Some ranch neighbor of his
from down in Texas.

1103
01:58:05,160 --> 01:58:08,493
Gonna split up with his wife
and come back here...

1104
01:58:09,264 --> 01:58:10,629
so he says.

1105
01:58:12,467 --> 01:58:14,799
But, like most of
Jack's ideas...

1106
01:58:16,638 --> 01:58:18,367
never come to pass.

1107
01:58:21,510 --> 01:58:25,378
I kept his room
like it was when he was a boy.

1108
01:58:26,782 --> 01:58:28,909
I think he appreciated that.

1109
01:58:33,455 --> 01:58:36,652
You are welcome to go up
to his room, if you want.

1110
01:58:42,331 --> 01:58:44,629
Yeah, I'd like that.
Thank you.

1111
02:01:45,811 --> 02:01:47,403
Tell you what.

1112
02:01:49,915 --> 02:01:53,646
We got a family plot.
He's goin' in it.

1113
02:01:56,321 --> 02:01:57,583
Yes, sir.

1114
02:02:00,192 --> 02:02:02,490
You come back
and see us again.

1115
02:02:16,808 --> 02:02:18,298
Thank you, ma'am.

1116
02:03:13,064 --> 02:03:14,998
##

1117
02:03:16,100 --> 02:03:18,762
Hey there, Junior.
Hey, Daddy.

1118
02:03:27,612 --> 02:03:28,909
Come here.

1119
02:03:31,716 --> 02:03:33,183
Like the car?

1120
02:03:33,651 --> 02:03:36,449
Yeah. Is it yours?
It's Kurt's.

1121
02:03:37,188 --> 02:03:40,282
I thought you were
seein' Troy.
Troy?

1122
02:03:40,857 --> 02:03:43,087
Daddy, that was two years ago.

1123
02:03:44,527 --> 02:03:46,825
Troy still playing baseball?

1124
02:03:47,197 --> 02:03:50,394
I don't know what he's doing.
I'm seein' Kurt now.

1125
02:03:50,800 --> 02:03:53,963
Well, what does Kurt do?
Works out in the oil fields.

1126
02:03:55,739 --> 02:03:59,072
So he's a roughneck, huh?
Yeah.

1127
02:03:59,909 --> 02:04:03,743
I guess you're 19,
you can do whatever you want.
Isn't that right?

1128
02:04:03,813 --> 02:04:05,110
Sure.

1129
02:04:13,723 --> 02:04:16,783
Daddy,
you need more furniture.
Yeah, well...

1130
02:04:17,427 --> 02:04:20,260
if you got nothin',
you don't need nothin'.

1131
02:04:24,534 --> 02:04:26,502
So, what's the occasion?

1132
02:04:30,940 --> 02:04:32,430
Me and Kurt...

1133
02:04:33,743 --> 02:04:35,608
we're getting married.

1134
02:04:38,381 --> 02:04:39,780
Well...

1135
02:04:40,583 --> 02:04:43,108
So how long have you
known this guy for?

1136
02:04:43,286 --> 02:04:44,753
About a year.

1137
02:04:46,756 --> 02:04:50,123
Our wedding will be June 5,
at the Methodist church.

1138
02:04:50,426 --> 02:04:54,226
Jenny will be singing
and Monroe is gonna cater
the reception.

1139
02:05:00,703 --> 02:05:02,694
Now this Kurt fella...

1140
02:05:05,040 --> 02:05:06,507
he loves you?

1141
02:05:09,278 --> 02:05:10,870
Yeah, Daddy.

1142
02:05:12,147 --> 02:05:13,546
He loves me.

1143
02:05:21,590 --> 02:05:23,615
Was hopin' you'd be there.

1144
02:05:26,395 --> 02:05:27,521
Yeah.

1145
02:05:30,799 --> 02:05:35,293
I think I'm supposed to be
on a roundup down near
the Tetons.

1146
02:05:56,225 --> 02:05:57,817
You know what?

1147
02:05:59,161 --> 02:06:02,220
I reckon they can find
themselves a new cowboy.

1148
02:06:04,031 --> 02:06:07,558
My little girl,
getting married.

1149
02:06:21,182 --> 02:06:23,241
To Alma and Kurt.

1150
02:07:43,730 --> 02:07:45,527
Jack, I swear...

